caption: Best meal EVER, not to be missed in Williamsburg
One of my favorite places for brunch in Williamsburg. The owner is sweet and kind. A very European vibe right on the heart of Bedford Ave. If they have the shakshuka on the menu -- get it!

This place is a gem. Food is great, vibe is great, and the store is cute! Sami, the owner is lovely and helpful. SUPER RECOMMENDED!!! Prices are normal and food quality is top. Love hanging out here with my friends.

love this spot! serving authentic food from the Maghreb. the vegetables in the tagine is perfectly caramelized and so nourishing. i had the tchotchuka with bread baked in house.  also the gift shop is perfectly curated, full of locally crafted goods and creative vintage home decor. 100% recommend!
Tagine is served in a traditional clay vessel. It’s A+ on a cold day.
Love this place, the food, the atmosphere, the staff are 😚👌

Adorable, quiet, and superb French/ North African food run by fantastic and funny chef for over 15 years. This place is a take away staple with great wine by the bottle to go. The brunch is not to be missed!
We love this place “can’t wait to come back”!
Such a lovely place. The owner and staff were welcoming & friendly. I ordered the couscous with lamb sausage and it did not disappoint. Will definitely be coming back!
Excellent food. Great playlist. Exceptional service. Consistently an all around wonderful experience.
A New York gem. The food is consistently incredible as is the service. The presentation is also gorgeous. Definitely going back.
Amazing food. Beautiful, charming, intimate ambiance. I look forward to my weekly visits. Thank gd for the heated patio! ❤️❤️
This place is the best! Fresh food, cool wines,  in house made breads... you name it! I love it! And Sam the owner is the coolest! Check out the store she has!
Incredible food, fantastic stories. Have always had the best times here.  Please go visit!
Simple is definitely a NYC staple. The service is friendly and the  food is fantastic. Brunch is a must and I especially like the vegetable tagine. Highly recommend.

I think one reviewer who wrote the following said it well: "The owner should change the name from Simple to Simply Delicious"  This is a nice little hole in the wall that looks like it is a treasure & labor of love. Anything you get here is generally awesome. They sort of pick from Algerian, French & American foods. I'm new to Algerian food, so I got to experiment a bit.  During COVID it has been more difficult to get a table sometimes, but worth the wait.

The food here is beyond delicious. Just like the name, they use simple ingredients but the flavors are deep and rich. I always feel super nourished after eating here. You can tell the food is prepared with love.

I used to live around the corner from Simple, and I miss it so much! This authentic French-Algerian restaurant is located on a quaint corner in Williamsburg, Brooklyn. Everything on the menu is amazing, but some of my favorites are the lemon & ricotta pancakes, kale salad and tagine. The vibe is cozy and welcoming, with a heated patio and small shop where you can purchase thoughtful goods for your home. Come for brunch or dinner, and be sure to pick up a loaf of fresh bread - it is baked in house!
Love this place, from a warm environment to the best flavours, Samy is a most charming host and a great chef.

I’ve been a customer at this restaurant for years and have always loved the food. The pancakes are unbelievable! Highly recommend. The owner is also the best human - cares so much about her business and her customers experience. Rare thing to find in the city.

I ordered French toast, and I literally got pancakes dipped in syrup, it was so bad I had to throw it out. First of all it wad brunt and 2nd of all how do you give a pancake and just call it French toast. The decoration was amazing no complains on that but the taste was extremely bad. The inside was so blend no taste whatsoever. I usually never give one star but this was literally my worst experience. I personally hate wasting food but with this one I had no other choice but to throw it out. I thought this spot was known for their French toast thus I wanted to stop by and see what was the hype was about. Probably, never coming back again. Wouldn't even recommend it to my worst enemy.

We met with friends at this place for dinner. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was a winning. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we shall absolutely come back again. Keep it up.
Awesome vegetable soup!! And nice People...
Excellent service, tasty food, and the cutest plates and cups. Hidden gem!
Lovely little algerian French place for brunch with a good number of tasty meat free options. Their coffees (hot, iced vietnamese and Espresso based) were great too.

The owner should change the name from Simple to Simply Delicious, because that's exactly what it was. Our meals we're very well seasoned and flavorful. Service was excellent. The owner was very attentive to everyone's needs and desires. The ambiance was very cozy and the music playlist was on point (French Hip Hop). We had no complaints whatsoever. Will definitely be going back again. 👌🏾
Prices fair very good options eco friendly straws
This spot constantly delivers. They serve excellent dishes for affordable prices, there are no long waits even when the place is packed.

Cute little gem in Williamsburg. The owner is lovely. A restaurant/cafe and a small gift shop.  Kale salad and steak was my fav! The tagine was good but the chef mistakenly made a vegetarian version instead of the chicken. They took it back to add chicken but it came out tasting weird (overcooked and slightly sandy in texture). Tasted much better when it firs came out.

They charge 16$ for the borek on seamless and it looks nothing like the picture. It was significantly smaller and less appetizing than advertised. Extremely oily.. small container of babaganoush. Algerian salad is just soggy lettuce and tomatoes. Terrible experience. Not worth the money.
Great find, great food!!

One of the coziest terrace in Williamsburg! Always loved this place, with their curated home goods shop- and with their beautifully designed outdoor sitting, can’t wait to go back there! Make sure to order the lamb merguez sandwich!

I meet with friends this lovely place quite a bit! This is my favorite restaurant to dine.  I go there many times. The meals are great, the staff is welcoming and the prices are affordable. I like being in this restaurant to have a decent supper.
Fantastic food, kind staff, consistently  awesome atmosphere. They charge fair pricing and the food quality is excellent. I recommend this place.
Awesome food. Get there before 11 to avoid the crowd.
My favorite corner in Bedford Av. The food always tastes like home, very nice ambience and great customer service Best babaganoush in NYC
Good food , bad service !!!
Awesome breakfast. Very small restaurant,  so expect a wait.

So, my best friend and I were walking down Bedford when we happened to stumble upon Simple. Walking through the door, we were greeted by an inviting, French/Algerian-inspired cafe. Don't be fooled by the name of this restaurant, because the food is anything but simple. I had the Croque Madame sandwich, served open-faced, and a side salad with radishes. The sandwich was made to perfection, and the salad had so many subtle flavors. The staff was so accommodating and attentive. I will be back.
👍 always my favorite place to visit in Williamsburg. Food is amazing!
I love this place so much! Nice food and the service is really great, friendly and professional!

The food was good, unfortunately that didn't reflect to their service. When we got the bill with fixed 20% service charged on it, we were surprised because it was never mentioned by our waiter. The worst was the waiter responded that all tables are charged 20% service, while the other table told us they did not get charged on their bill. It was unbelievably the waiter further told us that they charge service fee to certain tables because sometimes people don't tip well. When we asked how do they determine which tables get picked for service fee, he flipped out and just said okay he will refund and walked away... Overall a very unpleasant experience with the service.

The food was actually not bad, but our waiter was one of the worst i've seen in my life. During the brunch, he never stop by to check if things were okay not even refill the waters. We were a little surprised that there was a 20 % service fee added to our bill. When asked about the service fee, the waiter told us that they add 20% to EVERY table and "do you have a problem?"(direct quote). After the waiter left, tables next to us were kind enough to let us know that there were no service fee on their bill. So we asked the waiter again for the service fee, he changed his response to "sometimes people don't tip well therefore we charge service fee to certain tables."  I understand restaurant add service fee to a big party but we were only party of 3, it was a bit ridiculous to add a 20٪ service fee.
Best Brunch in Brooklyn. Food is delicious & fresh moroccan mint tea is a must 👌🏾

Best brunch spot in Williamsburg. Food is delicious and the staff is a total gem. There’s a small shop adjacent to the restaurant with gorgeous jewelry, candles and other decorative items everyone will want in his house. French Algerian cuisine that will blow your mind and your tastebuds. Last but not least, prices are beyond reasonable for the neighborhood, and the quality of the food makes it a total steal.
Good food, small place but enjoyable.  The wait staff are ok.

(Translated by Google) A very cool place for brunch, although somewhat small. For $ 20 you can eat buffet where you serve your taste bacon, eggs, casseroles, cheese, sweet vegetables, etc. The staff is not very friendly but loved the experience.  (Original) Un sitio muy chulo para hacer un brunch, aunque algo pequeño. Por 20 dólares tienes buffet libre en el que te sirves a tu gusto bacon, huevos, vegetales gratinados, queso, dulces, etc. El personal no es muy amable pero la experiencia nos encantó.
The worst service possible. Avoid at all costs.
(Translated by Google) Beautiful. Excellent attention. Delicious food and proposal.  (Original) Hermoso. Excelente atención. Riquísima comida y propuesta.

I love Simple Cafe! The food options are plentiful, high quality, and delicious. I always have a difficult time choosing what to have! We have eaten here many times and its always consistent, which I appreciate. The staff is helpful, friendly, and accommodating. They also have an amazing mango mimosa! Check out their cute little shop before you leave!
I had a great afternoon having a lovely glass of rosé. Will be back. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND.
Love this spot, good vibes.
My favorite spot in Brooklyn. Always amazing food and staff
Love this place! I love the chicken banh mi and my son goes crazy for the pancakes. The servers are incredibly nice and efficient and the vibe is chill and really comfortable.

Service was not good, the guy forgot our orders and we had to wait 1 hour and a half. The girl was nice and she bring us some bread and cake to apologize. Portion is very poor: 15$ for basically an empty plate as you can see form the picture.
Stopped in for a coffee -- beautiful setting, nice service, calming ambiance. Definitely bookmarked for future dinners/engagements
Great place. The buffet is perfect. The service as well.

The service seems to get a bad rep, but we had no problems at our brunch today. Good deal on the buffet with quality choices like ham, cheese, yogurt, croissants, potatoes and bacon, plus a serving of scrambled eggs made to order. We lingered a long time after finishing our food and did not feel rushed out. Very European in its vibe and approach. I will say the coffee is a bit overpriced considering you can go to good nearby coffee shops and get the same for less, but for the atmosphere and great people watching, it was worth it.

The food was really good heads down. Unfortunately the service was really cold and unpleasant. Overall my suggestion would be for the servers to have a change in attitude and it would increase the chances for clients to come back.
Solid breakfast
I actually enjoy the dishes and service, fantastic location right next to my house. The cashiers are always very nice. I highly recommend this place.

Unespected. If you have doubts looking cafe from external,  don't hesitate. The quality of the food is extraordinary. At first glance, buffet seems limited, but there are everything you need. Service is nice and courtesy fare. Thanks guy for all.

Quality ingredients and a really chill atmosphere, this was a delightful surprise for my lunch break. I saw catfish vermicelli listed on the menu and I knew I had to go in and give it a shot. Would have appreciated a slightly bigger portion but the flavor made up for it in spades. Prices are fitting for the area; a bit too high to go often, but good enough I'll definitely be back.

Great service, really cool atmosphere, and has a unique feel to it that's different from many other restaurants. Also, the look of the food was amazing. I enjoyed my steak and eggs as well, however there wasn't much steak given.

Service was amazing and friendly. The food was not as good as I imagined, but still good. Felt it was highly priced for the quality of the food. I got steak and eggs and it was good, but the steak was tiny.

5/5 and I’m happy to say it.  Went for: low key brunch with GF.  Food: Steak and eggs - healthy portion! Steak was cooked to point and marinated flavors were spectacular. Potato side was a pleasant surprise. Haveayner (sp?) Sandwich + Bacon: awesome!! Bread was perfect and flavors of egg, bacon, and avocado blended perfectly. Side salad was the right move.  Bloody Mary’s: excellent. Nothing crazy, very classic. Only has one type of Vodka. But it was great.
A friend of mine told me how good the buffet was and they were not wrong. I love going to local places. This one is particularly unique in its rich food and decor. Will definitely come back.
Food is good ...and taste healthy....
Everything was average. I had ricotta pancakes,which do not taste as good as they look. The shop was cute though.
Very good service...
French brunch buffet with really good food choice (the best Gratin dauphinois!!) All you can eat, with coffee and juice ... for only $20. Awesome
Half decent place, I would go some place else

This was one of the first places my husband and I had brunch when we moved to the neighborhood. We go almost every weekend now and always bring friends who are visiting here. Our friends would then always want to encore and end up bringing their friends, and we would bump into people here. Sammy and Fred are like old friends.
Terrible service. Wrong order after a 39 min wait. No acknowledgement of mistakes.  Super disappointing.
Awesome spot,  had steak and eggs that were excellent.   The steak comes as cubed hanger steak. Very tender.  We will be back.

My best friend (who also happens to have several restaurants) was adamant we come and I'm so glad we did. Authentic French/Algerian with a Vietnamese twist here and there on a few dishes. The flavors are simple as advertised yet elegantly done with unique spices that I can't quite gather exactly. Maybe it's the presentation (each plate is different and straight from what i imagine a hard to find Moroccan market) but the vibe here transports you to another time and place that makes it hard to leave. You leave wanting more and yet so satisfied. Lastly, once you're finished eating, there is a small shop where you can find a token to take home to remember what an epic place this is.  Highly highly recommend.
A cosy and cute little stop. It had a great bustling vibe and the food was very tasty.

Cosy restaurant with a great north africain atmosphere The food is simple and incredible The menu also have a great vietnamien recipe. During the weekend The best brunch buffet in Bedford. Ave highly recommended

Out of 4 orders, 3 of them were incorrect. Our waiter tried to deny it until he couldn’t anymore, and when our food was finally ready 20 minutes later, the corgette omelette was inedible. Absolutely the saltiest thing I’ve ever eaten. We tried to save the meal, but the chocolate cake was more than half melted and it had actually started to separate so there was visible oil surrounding the chocolate mush. Hands down the worst brunch I’ve ever had. Such a disappointment
Good afro Caribbean food
(Translated by Google) It's just normal edible hahahaha The salad is delicious hahaha  (Original) 그냥 보통 먹을만하다 ㅋㅋㅋㅋ 샐러드는 맛있음 ㅋㅋㅋ

I love this corner French + Algerian restaurant! It has the most amazing food, organic wine and great energy. It is a staple in the neighborhood and never disappoints. Also a lovely curated store sits inside SIMPLE and is perfectly curated and beautiful.
Omg amazing. Great service and fast. The staff is super friendly and catered to my request with no contest.
The Simple poached eggs are an excellent choice. Cozy little place to hide from the heat.

A little gem in Brooklyn. The name speaks for itself. Simple yet à totale escape! We were there for brunch and the food was divine. The baked eggs were amazing. The French toast was magical. Everything was fresh and tasty and we all loved the different dishes we ordered. The staff was extremely nice and attentive. The only downside is the size of the establishment, it is very small so it's safer to book if you're a group of 4+. I really like the owner's little boutique at the entrance. Cherry on the cake, you feel like you just left to Algeria for a moment. I definitely recommend and will go back to try the rest of the menu!
Gorgeous place. You can eat breakfast or brunch.... Good service
Good food. Really good vegetarian options. Relaxed service. Sweet set up. Perfect for people watching.
Excellent quality breakfast good, french algerian
It’s bangin
The homemade bread used for the breakfast sandwich was delicious.
Wonderful food in a perfect casual neighborhood setting.

I definitely enjoyed my meal at simple. Went in on a Saturday and immediately got a table. Service was great. Music actually added to the experience, which doesn't always happen.  This plane nailed the healthy comfort food thing. I got the simple poached eggs that were light and airy but filling. I was pleasantly surprised that my meal came with a decent side salad. Veggies were fresh and the dressing had the air of a citrus vinegar eternity. I don't even love dressings but I enjoyed this one. Also had the chance to try the fried egg. Perfectly fluffy and a solid portion.  While there is an all you can eat brunch buffet option, there are not bottomless drinks available which was disappointing. The bloody Mary was solid. Not too spicy but lots of flavor. Could have used more garnish. But that's honestly nit picking.  Overall I had a very satisfying experience. I would definitely recommend this place and will be back for more tasty foodstuffs.
Good brunch very tasty
Truly excellent food and service. Family friendly. A gem.
Good, hearty food and friendly service. Cozy place, great for a rainy Sunday morning
(Translated by Google) Very good place, hearty dishes and very warm service.  (Original) Muy buen lugar, platos abundantes y muy cálida atención.

First and foremost..... The food is outstanding.... As long as you don't mind poor service to go with it. Where to begin. The doorway was obstructed and we struggled to get through the door. We were second to arrive, and we waited over forty minutes for our food. The first people to arrive ordered a few minutes before us, and ate paid and left before our food even arrived. The coffee machine was broken but they didn't tell us until after sitting down and removing all of our winter gear then tried to order coffee. How rude. The hostess left our table mid sentence not once, but twice to go do other things, then returned to continue her sentence. To their credit they didn't charge us for the drinks.
Great, healthy food. Indescribably tasty. Affordable, too.
Great buffet
Service is usually meh, food is ALWAYS fantastic. Obsessed with their in-house bread.
Very cute place and great brunch selection!
Amazing brunch buffet!
Very slow service, great food. Brunch buffet is $18.50, worth it.
Nice place with a variety of breakfasts!
Stopped here for a coffee and restroom break. End up having desert with my coffee. Both were above average. Staff was kind and helpful. Very cute cafe. Loved the decoration.
Simply stated, some of the best food at a reasonable price in Williamsburg can be found here. Go for the all-you-can-eat brunch buffet on Saturday and Sunday.
Love it

Pretty bad food. The rice vermicelli dish had soggy noodles...it's a pretty hard dish to get wrong.  The banh mi had a hard bread instead of a crusty soft bread which is the best thing about banh mi!  And the prices weren't too good for what you get either.
Have their buffet for brunch. very good and good deal!
I had a very delicious omelette and the staff is very friendly. Only the coffee was too strong for me.

Nice ambiance, decor and good brunch. Quite full but not too busy. The $16 brunch buffet was delicious and v good value. However, the service was not very friendly - our waitress didn't say hello or much else really. I also asked for eggs well cooked and they weren't. We will come back for the good food in a nice setting though.

Ok food but truly terrible service. We were the some of only people in the restaurant but we were ignored while the waitstaff looked at their phones, stood around chatting and did who knows what. Then, once we finally ordered the food, it took an eternity to arrive. It was as if the waitstaff and the kitchen staff were intentionally trying to move as slowly as possible. We will never go back there again! Awful!
Wonderful place
Food was ok but service was terrible
Great food! I loved the onion soup! Friendly & authentic staff!
Delicious and cheap, the buffet brunch is a must.
I have to agree with the other post, the food was OK although I only ordered the beet salad, but the service was horrendous. Too bad, because it's a really nice joint with a big open air window
Great place and food aswell , 5 star chef
The MOST expensive coffee I have ever had. Unfortunately it was as good as Starbucks. Otherwise the place looks nice.
Coffee and pancakes were rather nice. Overall experience was spoiled by a very unfriendly service. Also i don't like to get cheated on the change...
Really enjoyed a delicious buffet brunch here the selection is not huge but what is available is very nice and the atmosphere is good. Great alternative if you don't fancy a boozy one.

The food was great! Delicious and flavorful. The service however, SUCKED!!! The woman was non-attentive, didn't introduce herself, when she got to the table she just said "Are you ready?", No type of "How are you" or anything. She was super sweet and smiled a lot at my boyfriend but brushed me off several times. She never brought my drink but brought his and even offered him a REFILL. I was so disappointed. Especially because the server next to us was very nice, attentive, and on top of his tables. Wish we would have gotten him.

We went there a Saturday only for the $15 Breakfast Buffet. First, you should know that it mainly consist in a variety of French dishes such as French Onion Tart, Zucchini Gratin, Gratin dauphinois, French toast, Croissant, etc. On top of that, you also get the usual items of a breakfast (Jelly, Cereals, Nutella, etc.). And last but not least, BACON. Pretty much everything was delicious, except for the cheese but finding great cheese in the US is Mission Impossible anyway. We will definitely go again! This is a good place for the French person in desperate need of back-home-food of for the local in search of an original and tasty Brunch.
Food was great fresh

A bit disappointing. The food was not bad at all, but the amount the served, for the priced charged, for avocado toast would make any self-respecting Melbournite cry.  It was also served on a roll which didn't feel right - a couple of slices of good quality bread, well toasted, is what's needed here.
Nice brunch space
Best kale salad

REAL FOOD breakfast buffet. Breakfast buffet this morning using only a Google map search.  Arrived by train, short walk through great neighborhood. In the door I quickly scanned for the buffet trough which I didn't see. Oh no, all this traveling and I got it wrong? No buffet? Then I saw the two big serving containers.  Got seated and in under 30 seconds i was eating a croissant. That croissant sold me. This was a French croissant not an American one. It was the best croissant I've ever had.  Buffet was just as good with homemade everything - except the fruit...I think.  Bacon was FILL MY POCKETS BEFORE I LEAVE good. Potato au gratin, french toast, scrambled eggs, homemade bread, real jam, coffee, tea, pastries and some stuff I didn't even try.  For $14.50 this was well worth the trip. The quality of the food, real food, was what made this worth its money.  I overdid it with you he bacon and croissant and could not finish. I lucked out with a doggie bag.  I'm guessing this is a husband/wife owned place and the investment in its welfare really shows. Super good food and a very french cafe experience.  They even charged my phone while I was there. Nice to eat without electronics.  I will probably go back before you leave...only here for 5 days but still...bacon!

(Translated by Google) We had the buffet for breakfast! Super good and an affordable price! A service at the top and a beautiful decoration.  it's worth it to take 30 minutes to get there! and think of taking a walk in the neighborhood because there are beautiful "Murals"! I highly recommend this address!  (Original) Nous avons pris le buffet pour le petit déjeuner ! Super bon et un prix abordable ! Un service au top et une belle décoration.  ça vaut la peine de faire 30 minutes de métro pour y aller ! et pensez à faire un tour dans le quartier car il y'a de beaux "Murals" ! Je recommande chaudement cet adresse !
Sweet little french cafe with DELICIOUS food. The roast potatoes are 1st class. Eggs superb. Nice vibe too with kind french servers.
Great buffet brunch
great!
Very disappointing. Things are made with no care at all and the portions are tiny.

So hard to find great Vietnamese! We ate 4 days a week last week and will keep eating this week. Your business model is AMAZING!! Never have seating, just run through seamless and watch your business flourish
Great atmpophere and fantastic home made croissants.
Food is die for. Amazingly tasty and not expensive.

Overall underwhelming and due to the inattentive and surly staff, unpleasant. 'Havemeyer' sandwich unspeakably bland, and was strangely devoid of even pepper for seasoning. Fries overdone, greasy, dry, tasteless. Waitress unfriendly, waiter distracted. Waiter came out 20 mins after seating us-after the surly waitress finally DID take our order in his absence to ask if we HAD ordered yet...lol Terrible experience, skipping from now on.
Simple Cafe for simply good coffee. Not expensive and well maintained. The food is also delicious - love the home made bread.
